Interesting. Maybe app stores should show a helpful chart to explain the star rating, so that the results are more uniform.<p>In my case,<p>5 stars = Does exactly what I want;
4 stars = Does most of the things I want, minor features missing;
3 stars = Has a few useful features, the rest are irrelevant;
2 stars = Frequent crashes and major bugs;
1 star = Does not install or start at all no matter what I try (very rare).<p>I mostly give 4 stars, but there are a lot of 5 star worthy apps, as well (Pocket Informant and ES Explorer, for example).

Seems like you really have a lot of contrast in that theme.  Also I hope you will consider dropping the extra parentheses.<p>And instead of dropping CoffeeScript I hope you will try out ToffeeScript.  But just use the basic ! thing, you don&#x27;t need the other stuff like auto callback.<p><pre><code>    e, data1 = fs.readFile! &#x27;foo&#x27;
    e, data2 = redisclient.get! &quot;thekey&quot;
    console.log data1
    console.log data2</code></pre>
